        <section anchor="sec:solution" title="Adapt the transport initialization for the 0-RTT connections">

        <t>This memo proposes a solution where an additional parameter is registered during the 1-RTT phase to improve the initial throughput of the 0-RTT.</t>
	<t>The server measures the RTT during the 1-RTT handshake. When the server detects that the start of the connection is very slow, it stores in the session ticket a value of the IW which will increase the initial throughput when reconnecting.</t> 

	<t>When the client re-establishes the session using a 0-RTT phase the server receives the session ticket and decides or not [ADD REF]. When the server re-establishes the session it resuses the IW parameter it computed during the 1-RTT phase.</t>

	</section>

